# Caddy reverse proxy: terminates TLS (auto Let's Encrypt) and forwards wss://
# to the local game server. The wasm client (GitHub Pages, HTTPS) connects to
# wss://game.idletree.net and Caddy proxies it to the plain-ws server on :40001.
# reverse_proxy upgrades WebSocket connections automatically.
#
# Run on the machine hosting the server:
#   caddy run --config deploy/Caddyfile
#
# Requirements (see HOSTING.md):
#   - DNS A record game.idletree.net -> this machine's public IP, Cloudflare
#     DNS-ONLY (grey cloud) so Let's Encrypt can validate this origin.
#   - Router forwards TCP 80 + 443 to this machine.
#   - The game server is listening on 0.0.0.0:40001 (run-server.ps1).

game.idletree.net {
	reverse_proxy 127.0.0.1:40001
}
